  "text": "A previous study by De Jong et al. [CITATION_1] identified three modules, comprising 5,062 probes (mapping to 1,458 unique genes), that were associated with cyclic seasonal patterns. However, these probes were primarily driven by changes in red blood cells and platelets [CITATION_2] . Here, we did not identify cell type specific gene signatures for red blood cells, but instead identified enrichment for leukocytes markers. This difference could be attributed to the single-gene approach we employed and that we only shared 2,406 genes (18% of our dataset) with the De Jong et al. analysis [CITATION_3] .",
